data.text:
At Carolina

Played in Carolina's 80-20 victory over Old Dominion • Saw his first career action in the Idaho game in 2013, rushing twice with a long gain of two yards • Joined the team as a walk-on prior to the 2011 season • Smart quarterback who understands the spread offense.

Reynolds High School

Played football for four seasons, basketball for three and ran track for three • Guided his team to the state 4-A state championship in 2009 and was named MVP • Was the state 4-A championship game most outstanding performer in 2009 and 2010 • First-team All-Western N.C. in 2009 and all-conference in 2010 • Two-time team captain • Passed for 4,385 yards, 39 touchdowns and ran for 1,414 yards and 22 touchdowns during his career • Passed for 2,374 yards and 25 touchdowns as a senior.
